# Deployment Guide - Aus Weather Watch

**Full step-by-step instructions for deploying the Aus Weather Watch website to an AWS EC2 cloud server.**

This document records the complete process used to launch the cloud VM, install the web server, deploy the application, and make the site publicly accessible.

## 1. AWS EC2 Instance Setup

1. Log in to the [AWS Management Console](https://console.aws.amazon.com).
2. Navigate to **EC2** → **Launch instance**.
3. Configure the instance with the following settings:
   - **Name**: `aus-weather-watch-vm`
   - **AMI**: Ubuntu Server 24.04 LTS
   - **Instance type**: `t2.micro` (Free tier eligible)
   - **Key pair**: Create a new key pair (`aus-weather-key`) and download the `.pem` file
   - **Security group**:
     - Allow SSH (port 22) from Anywhere
     - Allow HTTP (port 80) from Anywhere
     - Allow HTTPS (port 443) from Anywhere
4. Launch the instance and wait until status is **Running**.
5. Allocate and associate an **Elastic IP** (so the public IP never changes when stopping/starting the instance).

## 2. Connect to the Server (SSH)

On your local machine, open PowerShell or Command Prompt and run:

```powershell
ssh -i "E:\aus-weather-key.pem" ubuntu@YOUR-ELASTIC-IP
3. Install Nginx Web Server
Bashsudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
sudo apt install nginx -y
sudo systemctl enable --now nginx
Verify Nginx is running:
Bashsudo systemctl status nginx
4. Deploy the Website
Bashcd /var/www
sudo rm -rf html
sudo mkdir html
cd html

# Clone the GitHub repository
sudo git clone https://github.com/Nathanthegunnero/ICT171-35567023.git .

# Navigate into the project folder
cd "Australian Weather Watch"

# Install dependencies and build the React app
npm install
npm run build

# Copy the built files to Nginx web directory
cd ..
sudo cp -r "Australian Weather Watch/dist/"* ./

# Set correct permissions
sudo chown -R www-data:www-data /var/www/html
sudo chmod -R 755 /var/www/html

# Restart Nginx
sudo systemctl restart nginx
5. Link Custom Domain (DNS)

Log into your domain registrar (Namecheap, Cloudflare, etc.).
Create an A record:
Host: @
Value: Your Elastic IP address

(Optional but recommended) Create a www record pointing to the same Elastic IP.
Wait for DNS propagation (usually 5–30 minutes).

After propagation, the site will be accessible at http://yourdomain.com.
6. Starting / Stopping the Server (Important for Credits)

Stop the instance when not in use to save credits.
Start the instance when needed.
After starting, the Elastic IP remains the same — no reconfiguration is required.
The website files and configuration are preserved on the EBS volume.

7. Verify the Site

Run curl ifconfig.me on the server to confirm the public IP.
Open a browser and visit http://YOUR-ELASTIC-IP or http://yourdomain.com.

The site should display the live Aus Weather Watch dashboard.

